    <h1 class="title">About PSearch Project</h1>
    
    <h2>Goal</h2> 

    <p>The goal of the <a href="http://psearch.ics.uci.edu">PSearch
    Project</a> is to make it easier to search for UCI People.  It has
    a single input search box, which allows keyword queries on people
    name, UCInetID, telephone number, department, and title. It has
    the following features:
    </p>

    <ul>
      <li><b>Supports interactive search</b>: search as you type;</li>
      <li><b>Allows minor errors in the keywords</b>;</li>
      <li><b>Supports synonyms</b>, e.g., "William = Bill", and "OIT
      = Office of Information Technology";</li>
      <li><b>Allows multiple keywords</b>.</li>
    </ul>
    
    <p>We use the UCI Directory data provided
    by <a href="http://www.oit.uci.edu">OIT</a>.</p>
    
